The South African Weather Service (Saws) on Thursday warned that the severe thunderstorms accompanied by heavy downpours which were observed over north-western KwaZulu-Natal are expected to move towards the north-east. Saws said the thunderstorms are expected to be accompanied by heavy downpours possible hail, strong winds and severe lightning. Areas which are expected to be affected include Abaqulusi, Alfred Duma - Indaka, Alfred Duma - Ladysmith, Big Five Hlabisa - Hlabisa, Big Five Hlabisa - Hluhluwe, Dannhauser, eDumbe, eMadlangeni, Endumeni, Inkosi Langalibalele - Escourt, Inkosi Langalibalele - Sobabili, Jozini, Mpofana - Giants Castle, Mpofana - Mooi River, Msinga, Mtubatuba, Newcastle, Nkandla, Nongoma, Nquthu, Okhahlamba, Ulundi, Umhlabuyalingana, Umvoti and uPhongolo. Localised damage to infrastructure especially informal settlements and rural areas is possible. Flooding of low-lying bridges, susceptible roads is also possible. Poor driving conditions due to slippery roads and poor visibility is possible which may result in minor vehicle accidents, warned the weather office.